  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Configuring Siri support"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To process user requests that originate from Siri, first add the Siri",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "capability to your app’s target. This informs the system that your app is",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "ready to resolve, confirm, and handle SiriKit intents, typically",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "through its Intents extension; in iOS 14 and later, you can choose to perform",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "each of these steps from within your app.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After you configure your app to process SiriKit intents, add code — to your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "delegate or your Intents extension — to route incoming intents to your custom",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "handlers. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/SiriKit/dispatching-intents-to-handlers",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "watchOS doesn’t support all intent types. For example, a watchOS app",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "can’t start a video call or handle intents in the CarPlay domain. Check an",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "intent’s availability information to determine whether you can use it on",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "watchOS.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-the-Siri-capability-to-your-target",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add the Siri capability to your target",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Follow the steps in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/adding-capabilities-to-your-app#Add-a-capability",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "add the capability to your app’s target, making sure you select the Siri",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "capability from Xcode’s Capabilities library. For watchOS apps with separate WatchKit",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "extensions, you must add the capability to the WatchKit Extension target. The",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "capability isn’t available for macOS.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "siri",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After you add the Siri capability, Xcode automatically updates the entitlements",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "file of your target to include the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BundleResources/Entitlements/com.apple.developer.siri",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The App Store requires this entitlement for any app that contains an Intents",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "extension that handles non-shortcut Siri requests.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Handle-SiriKit-intents-in-an-Intents-extension",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Handle SiriKit intents in an Intents extension",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use an Intents extension to respond to the user’s request from Siri quickly and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "without incurring the performance cost of loading the entire app into memory.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To use an extension, you must first complete a number of additional",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "configuration steps, such as adding one or more Intents extensions to your",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app’s target and specifying the types of intents those extensions support. For",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sirikit/intent_handling_infrastructure/creating_an_intents_app_extension#2864127",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Handle-SiriKit-intents-directly-in-your-app",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Handle SiriKit intents directly in your app",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In iOS 14 and later, you can choose not to use an Intents extension, and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "instead respond to the user’s request directly from within your iOS app. To do",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "this, override the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/UIApplicationDelegate/application(_:handlerFor:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "method in your app delegate and use it to map incoming intents to the objects",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that are capable of handling them.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the same way you configure an Intents extension, you must specify the types",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of intents that your iOS app supports. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sirikit/intent_handling_infrastructure/creating_an_intents_app_extension#2864128",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
